text: This picture gets me so mad

WotC: Commander 2020 will feature a three-mana commander that gains control of all enemy creatures each combat and forces them to attack their owners, whereupon you gain 20 life and make eight 6/6 tokens. There is also a seven-mana 1/1 that says you can cast artifacts as though they had flash. 

Command Zone: You definitely want to play the flash commander out of the box with this one

Just about every take I've seen on the Precons, from both places I respect and don't has made me a bit livid lately. Being a casual in a world of "X is the best, period" hot takes is fairly infuriating.
"you always want to do the flash thing, it just doesn't feel better than getting to cast thing at the end of your oppenents turns"
How about "play the commander that looks fun"
CZ gets a little high on their own supply at times
Impossible.
JLK is on the CAG.
I personally feel like Sevinne looks like the most fun.
Thank you, Dean. I needed that.

“This Boros deck has seventeen new cards that each cost two mana and deal 40 damage to your opponents, but looking at the stats, there are only 7 draw card spells, so this is clearly the weakest of the decks”

I used to think fairly highly of the Command Zone as it was the only real content I took in. Recently I started taking in a whole lot more content while at work via podcasts and I find myself disagreeing with them a whole lot now.
Yeah, they weren't the first podcast I cut from rotation, but they got cut pretty fast when I started expanding.
I tried them again recently and they plug their sponsors, Patreon _and_ they have ad spots now. That's just crazy
They'll never get another listen from me.

They recommended that Feather players run Orrery. That deck is 47 instants and a Commander. 

I still value their content, they didn’t get where they are by accident, but I like dana’s read. A little high on their own supply sometimes
They’re a fantastic on-ramp to the format, but once you have experience, I find people tend to outgrow the podcast a bit. Game Knights is great though.
I agree. I will still watch/listen to their content, but as I've been trying to train myself to be a better builder and evaluator of cards I feel like I don't value their advice as much.
Yeah, I did recommend them, and specifically Game Knights to my cousin's boyfriend to get him into the format.
Game Knights is the most entertaining of the gameplay videos you can watch but a lot of the real interesting stuff comes from the guests. You can always bet on an Orrery coming out from Josh.

“Pramikon is bad, don’t play them.”

“This deck struggles against early aggressive since it spins its wheels a lot and folds to pressure. Play Bloodthirsty Blade.”
Wat
I'm turning it on now.

They also said the Rakdos deck needed more reanimator effects to win, but advised against playing Chainer. 

That said I hate Pramikon a lot so I’m all for ripping it in half. I mean, tossing it out of the deck.
it also doesn't help that they don't actually like aggro, so I can't imagine they play the deck all that well
Like, I get why the pick Elsha, she is genuinely the safest pick, but like, their thoughts and suggestions seems somewhat counterintuitive at times
Please don’t speak ill of our geometry overlord, Joseph.
They’re doing their best.
It’s not a geometry overlord, it’s a bad LSD trip
Same difference...

:eyes: :sweat_drops:

I will say, the art could be a bit more clear, but the foil will look :ok_hand:
I mean that art looked just as good on my parent’s old PC screensaver so I agree
Exactly! They just perfected this kind of art. It brings a tear to my eye every time.
And no, it’s not because of the shine and glare burning my retinas
Gotta love that windows 95 art I guess
I like Elsha and Sevinne, I just don’t like them more than Kykar
Much nostalgia.
It feels awkward to have just gotten commanders in these colors
I wish Sevinne did a bit more, since copying the spell isn’t always great, but anything is better than nothing. Kykar is fantastic though.
A better, flying Young Pyromancer? I’m in all day
I’m actually surprised people don’t like Sevinne more. I know I have a graveyard bias but people usually like doubling stuff
I think it may have to do with some of the lack luster options available to copy. If you want to close out a game there are only three or four options available.
That’s why Zetalpa is in the precon :T
I'm with you there, Joey. My first EDH deck was my boy The MImeoplasm.
Zetalpa still bothers me.
YEAH MIMEO

Zetalpa was put in the precons for the Sultai deck to have a Rayami target. That’s... irksome. 

Sevinne isn’t the way the deck wins, but hey, neither was Aminatou. They just facilitate a solid value train to inch your way to victory. I’m still surprised people don’t like it. Each year we get a controlling deck that *looks* like it’s difficult to win with. K&T, Aminatou, Sevinne. Everyone complained the Wizards deck in 2017 was impossible to win with, but it was the spikiest of the four decks. 

I dunno, I don’t have a real point here, I’m just kinda monologuing about weird consistencies among us players. We like value but also ignore it when it stares us in the face.
I think I'm personally bothered by Zetalpa being in there because I was staring at my 5 copies in my binder, then saw I was going to get another one in the precon I ordered.
So I'm not saying it's useless entirely, I just don't need another one. Lol

The only reason why I push back a bit against your resining for Zetalpa is because I think there is only 1 way for the Sultai deck to “kill” them in Mire in Misery if I’m not mistaken. And that’s a pretty bad way to try and kill that monster. 

I just don’t know what Sevinne does that other decks can’t do better. I still really like them, but the three main win cons that I can see (Devil’s Play, Increasing Confusion, and Increasing Devotion) are something you have to jump through hoops for in order to get a decent effect.
Pramikon flicker is going to be a cool deck.
I like Sevinne’s Reclamation a lot, but another flashback spell or two that could win the game could be nice. Or something else with WAR Ral’s passive
YES IT IS
IT’S GOING TO BE GREAT
If those are the only three win conditions you see in that deck, Angelo, I’m gonna have to revoke your Jesguy title
Throw in some Avatar of Slaughter effects, some flicker and bounce... Mmmm
Adding a single copy of past in flames to the precon would have gone a long way to helping sevinne feel like it can keep up in that precon environment
:thinking_face:
Not the only, but those seem to be the three most common that people are bringing up. I don’t feel like a Precon Commander should feel like a “trap”. Cause Sevinne kinda does.
How about more than a single copy, though.
Haha, i mean, that would be great too
Just don’t tell anyone
Yes and no. Since Sevinne only copies the first spell cast from a graveyard each turn, it only has limited usefulness imo
Flashback Dragon kinda works like Past in Flames for the deck.
Sure, that is true. It would have felt like you were winning with flashback at least
Maybe it’s just a feel thing? I dunno
I am glad that dragon exists
It should still be included, but the deck would have made more sense to throw in the Surveil spell from Guilds since they’re adding Standard cards to precondition now :T
It’s not a trap, it’s control. Come on

I understand it can facilitate control based decks, which I’m all for, but I’m not sure copying high costed spells from the yard is the best way to control. It’s a. Good way to control, no doubt, but a lot of the spells that you can flashback do lack a bit of teeth.
That being said, I am genuinely curious to your preferred wincons Joey. I’m going to be throwing together a Sevinne deck (of course) so the more opinions the better! x)

As much as I hate to agree with either Dean or Angelo, much less both at the same time I really do think a combat control Pramikon would be a silly way to build a pillow fort. Build it kind of like the Jeskai version of the spider thing from last year, force everyone to attack all the time but never attack you, flicker Pramikon with Deadeye and co. It's not going to discourage attacking because you're forcing it, you're just forcing everyone to hit everyone else...and hard
It's just making the decision of who to attack for everyone, rather than the dork you know that just sits there and "ok, I'mma roll this dice to decide"

text: Negative attention is still attention
You love agreeing with me, Matt, don't deny it
As much as I hate agreeing with you, I hate agreeing with that golgari slug podcast host of mine even more
I'm glad to see the Pramikon take. Everyone has been criticizing it as bad Moat, when it honestly can do a whole lot more while still steering people in other directions.

Also, if your LGS is doing the "have to play the Precons" prerelease thing in spite of Wizards trying to wuss out on it and making it into a feel-bad-fest, I honestly think Pramikon is the best Commander for Jeskai in that environment.
It's what I'm going to be playing, anyway.
I do like Joeys observation that it might not lend itself to decks that create interesting game states though
I like that it can enable corner case strategies by pivoting the table a certain way, but that can also enable degenerate or dumb things too, which is definitely a downside.
